Depends on:
	scikit-learn > v17

The sex_classifier node listens on topic 'voice_activity' which the node that detects voice
publish on when some voice activity is detected. 

The vad publishes a frame of audio it thinks contains voice activity. 
after which this node does some feature extraction and svm classification. 

After classification is done, result is published on the 'opencog/speaker_sex/' topic
along with simple confidence percentage.

The trained model is located in the 'model' directory. It's a pickle binary format. 

